HEADWORD: Esplees
<hw>Es*plees"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>expletia</ets>, OF. <ets>espleit</ets>. Cf.
<er>Exploit</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The full profits
or products which ground or land yields, as the hay of the meadows, the
feed of the pasture, the grain of arable fields, the rents, services,
and the like.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

